  "dcterms:abstract": "Takotsubo cardiomyopathy (TTC) is defined as a reversible, acute ventricular dysfunction without any evidence of coronary artery obstruction. This case report examines the first instance of TTC caused by pulmonary tuberculosis, discussing diagnostic criteria, patient symptoms, and treatment approach, illustrating the relationship between stressors and TTC symptoms.",
  "schema:datePublished": "2014-03-01",
  "schema:keywords": [
    "Takotsubo Cardiomyopathy",
    "Tuberculosis",
    "Pulmonary",
    "Catecholamines"
  ],
  "fabio:hasPublicationVenue": {
